title: Aaron Shafer Memorial RR and Time Trial
Music City Crits
description: Wednesday Night Criterium Racing in Nashville, TN also known as Music City Crits
course: 6 Turn course setup on the TN State Fairgrounds Speedway Track
registration: Online Registration via USA Cycling for $20 plus online fee or $25 Onsite.
notes:
•	Online pre-reg closes at 12 PM Central on Wednesday for Wednesday races.
•	Wednesday Entry fees: Online pre-reg $20 + $2.40 fee - - Day of registration $25 - 2nd race on same day $10. 
•	If there is a rainout & you pre-reg’d, then your entry applies to the next race. 
•	If you pre-register & there is no rain out but you do not show up then there are NO REFUNDS. 
•	Junior age riders race for FREE in the Junior Race ONLY. Juniors racing in higher categories races must pay registration fee.  Must have annual license or purchase a one-day. 
•	Race day registration opens at 4:30 PM on Wednesdays.
•	Wednesday night field size limit: 50 racers in Cat 5 & 75 in all other fields. 
•	Payouts and primes must be picked up weekly. If not, your prize is forfeited and put back into the pot for primes. 
•	Awards will be given to winners of the overall in each category & the team omnium competition.
•	You must present your USA Cycling license & issued bib number each week. 
•	Please use the same number each week to race. DO NOT WASH THEM! $5 fee to replace lost or forgotten numbers. 
•	Championship awards ceremony follows final race on August 27th (free food & podium presentation).
•	1 race drop rule will be used so overall results will be based on your best 11 races.
•	USAC Rule 4C4(a) points system each week towards overall series points, top 25 earn points 
•	Tiebreakers decided according to USAC rules 
•	Wheel pit area provided, wheel in/wheel out, USAC free lap rule applies 
•	One-Day and Annual license applications available at registration, $15 and $70 respectively 
•	$3.60 of every entry fee goes to USAC insurance surcharge & $1 per entry to TBRA
•	NO TBRA Road Series points awarded for all dates.
•	Promoter reserves the right to cancel due to rainy weather. 
•	All NEWS & RAINOUT info will be posted on Music City Crits Facebook page @ https://www.facebook.com/musiccitycrits and on twitter @musiccitycrits
directions:
Everyone is encouraged to arrive via the Craighead Street entrance and enter at the tunnel gate located at the back side of the track.  Drive through the tunnel and park in the infield area.  You’ll have a great view of the entire course from the infield.  This will allow your car and bikes to be in a safe area inside the track.  The men’s and women’s restrooms, as well as port-a-johns, will also be available inside the track infield area.  There is plenty of room for spectators, so invite all your friends and family to see you race.  This venue is very spectator friendly.  

All races will be held at the TN State Fairgrounds Speedway
625 Smith Avenue, Nashville TN 37203

title: Calfkiller Ride To The Sky
description: The 2nd annual Calfkiller Ride To The Sky will be bigger and better than last years event.  The routes are the same as last year, with the addition of a 46 mile route.  The 22 and 62 mile route are the same as last year, and the 46 mile is a mixture of the two.  All routes showcase the beauty that the Cumberland Plateau has to offer with scenic view, tough climbs and very little automobile traffic.  Along with the new route we are adding overall timing and a King and Queen of the mountain timing.   All riders will receive an event goodie bag along with an event t-shirt.  Post ride activities will include award winning BBQ (Papa Tony's), beverages (Calfkiller Brewing Co.) and live music.
course: The 22 mile route will be challenging but rewarding with beautiful scenery and well manned rest stops. The 46 and 62 mile after splitting off from the 22 mile group will start their first climb of the day which will be timed for King and Queen of the mountain. After this climb the route winds around the country side to the 2nd rest stop at Calfkiller Brewery (don't bypass this stop, it's a good one). Shortly after this stop the 46 mile loop will split off and start making their way back to the start finish line. This return for them is full of rolling hills and a little climb we call Smiley Face. After this stop the 62 mile riders will ride along the countryside through rolling back roads till they reach Calfkiller Hwy where the rollers get a little more challenging until you reach the second climb of the day. This one is a long beautiful climb that will take you to the top and the edge of the Cumberland Plateau. From here it’s all down hill…kind-of. All routes will return to the starting point at Nashville State Community College Cookeville Campus
registration: Register online at USA Cycling.  On-site registration is available, and it opens at 7AM (central time).
